Doda Conrad (19 February 1905 – 28 December 1997) was a Polish-born American bass operatic singer.

The son of Marya Freund, Conrad studied singing with Emilio de Gogorza in New York, then made his debut in Paris in 1932 at the École normale de musique de Paris and the Théâtre de la Porte-Saint-Martin.
